On one hand, it seems that there is an experimental vaccine capable of reducing mortality from Ebola, but on the other hand, no drug has been found yet that has clearly proven to be suitable for treating the existing infection.
A cocktail of antibodies, ZMapp, initially showed promise in the field, but formal studies revealed a lower effectiveness than hoped for in preventing deaths.
In the PALM study, ZMapp was used as a control measure, meaning that scientists used it as a reference and compared it with the other three therapies.
USA Gymnastics supports the letter from the United States Olympic Committee and recognizes the absolute necessity for the Olympic community to work towards creating a safe environment for all its athletes.
We agree with what the USOC stated, namely that the interests of our athletes and our clubs, and of their sport, can be better served by moving forward with a significant change within our organization, rather than through decertification.
USA Gymnastics has promoted an independent investigation to understand how it was possible that an abuse of the dimensions described with such courage by those who managed to survive Larry Nassar remained hidden for so long, and is willing to implement any necessary or appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and USOC have the same goal: to make gymnastics and other sports as safe as possible, so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a reliable, positive, and accountable environment.
