The 802.11n standard can operate in both the 2.4GHz and 5.0GHz bands.
Assuming the base station has dual radios, this will allow it to be backward compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b, and 802.11g.
802.11n speeds are considerably higher compared to those of previous versions, with a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbps.
